message.content: Hey, I'm here to see you for my illness.
I've been feeling unwell.
Hello there. What's your name? I'm doctor Ibrahim.
Oh, it's nice to meet you, Dr. Ibrahim.
I'm Amelia. I must say, I'm rather pleased you asked for my name.
It's refreshing to be treated with a touch of courtesy.
Now, about my condition... I've been feeling quite dreadful lately.
Would you be a dear and help me figure out what's wrong? 3
Hey, Amelia. It's nice to meet you. I'm sorry to know that this happened to you. Could you tell me more about what you feel?
Well, Dr. Ibrahim, I appreciate your sympathy, though I must say your tone seems a bit... off.

Nevertheless, I'll indulge you. I've been feeling absolutely dreadful - my body aches, and I'm just not myself. It's as if I'm trapped in a fog of discomfort. Surely, a doctor of your caliber can deduce what's ailing me without too much prodding? 4
Well, after all, I can't know how you feel if I'm not you. Hence, we'll need to work together to figure out what's going on with you.
Seems as if you're just not feeling well. I think you might have a fever,
A fever? Really, Dr. Ibrahim?
I suppose that could explain this wretched feeling.
But are you quite certain?
I mean, I expected a more... thorough examination before jumping to conclusions.
Perhaps you could elaborate on why you think it's a fever?
I'd hate to be misdiagnosed, you understand.
Well, when you entered and you had to take a temperature, it seems as if the the patient staff has flagged up to me that your temperature was thirty eight point six degrees. Think that's really high.
Oh, I see. Well, I suppose that does sound rather high, doesn't it?
Though I must admit, I'm a bit flustered that you didn't mention this crucial detail earlier.
You been drinking enough lately?
Oh, I see. Well, I suppose that temperature reading does sound rather high.
As for my drinking habits, Dr. Ibrahim, I hardly see how that's relevant.
But since you asked so... charmingly, I'll have you know I've been far too miserable to keep track of my fluid intake.
Now, what do you propose we do about this alleged fever of mine? 3
It seems as if you might need to take a bit of time from work. So perhaps a few days of rest, just drink up a lot a lot more. We're gonna give you some top grade paracetamol. It sound good to you?
Rest and fluids? Is that really all you have to offer, Dr. Ibrahim?
I expected something more... revolutionary from a medical professional.

And paracetamol? How terribly ordinary. Are you absolutely certain this will suffice? I mean, I'm not one to doubt your expertise, but I do hope you're not simply dismissing my concerns. Perhaps you could explain how these simple remedies will actually help me recover from this dreadful fever? 2
